.TH MCX 1 "March 2026" "MaxCompression 2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mcx \- high\-ratio lossless data compression tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mcx compress
[\fB\-l\fR \fILEVEL\fR]
[\fB\-o\fR \fIOUTPUT\fR]
\fIINPUT\fR
.br
.B mcx decompress
[\fB\-o\fR \fIOUTPUT\fR]
\fIINPUT\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mcx
compresses and decompresses files using the MaxCompression (MCX) format.
It achieves compression ratios competitive with xz/LZMA2 while beating
bzip2 on all file types.
.PP
MCX uses a hybrid approach: BWT (Burrows\-Wheeler Transform) for text
and structured data, LZRC (LZ + Range Coder) for binary archives.
Smart detection automatically selects the best strategy.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-level =\fILEVEL\fR
Compression level (1\-26). Default: 3.
.RS
.TP
.B 1\-3
Fast mode (LZ77 + FSE). Speed: 15\-50 MB/s.
.TP
.B 6\-9
Standard mode (LZ\-HC + adaptive entropy). Speed: 3\-15 MB/s.
.TP
.B 10\-22
Best mode (BWT + multi\-table rANS). Speed: 1\-5 MB/s.
.TP
.B 26
Ultra mode (LZRC v2.0 engine). Speed: 0.5\-1.7 MB/s.
Best ratio on binary data.
.RE
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output =\fIFILE\fR
Output file path. If not specified, appends .mcx for compression
or removes .mcx for decompression.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Compress a file at maximum level:
.B mcx compress \-l 20 data.bin \-o data.mcx
.TP
Decompress:
.B mcx decompress data.mcx \-o data.bin
.TP
Fast compression:
.B mcx compress \-l 1 largefile.tar
.SH COMPRESSION RATIOS
Typical results on the Silesia benchmark corpus (211 MB):
.PP
.TS
l l l l l.
Tool	Ratio	Speed (comp)	Speed (decomp)
_
mcx L20	4.35x	0.5\-1.7 MB/s	12\-19 MB/s
xz \-9e	4.34x	2\-5 MB/s	50\-80 MB/s
bzip2 \-9	3.37x	5\-8 MB/s	5\-10 MB/s
gzip \-9	2.73x	15\-30 MB/s	200+ MB/s
.TE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error (invalid input, I/O error, decompression failure).
.SH FILES
MCX files use the
.B .mcx
extension and begin with magic bytes
.BR "MCX\\x01" .
